rounds.response:
[Player 1] Now the central column and the top row are both owned entirely by O and X respectively, so this is the last move before somebody wins. I observe:

- If I pick 6, I’ll have a diagonal X in 0 + 4 (blocked) + 6, but 4 is already taken by O.  
- If I pick 7, I get 2 + 5, but 5 is open—still not an immediate win.  
- The only line still open to me is the bottom row 6–7–8, but 8 is O.

My only remaining tactical trick is to strike on the right side by taking 5, giving me X in 2 and 5, putting immediate pressure on both the 2-5-8 line and a possible 0-4-8 fork. If my opponent blocks, that will open another attacking path.

[5]
